'''Knut Markhus''' (7 November 1878 &ndash; 7 August 1963) was a Norwegian educator and politician.
He was born in [[Skånevik]]. He edited the newspaper ''[[Haugesunds Avis]]'' from 1911 to 1913. In 1913 he founded the [[folk high school]] {{ill|Sunnhordland folkehøgskule|no}}, where he eventually served as headmaster. He was elected to the [[Storting]] from [[Hordaland]] for the periods 1922&ndash;1930 and 1937&ndash;1945, representing the [[Liberal Party (Norway)|Liberal Party]]. He chaired [[Noregs Mållag]] from 1936 to 1946.<ref name=allkunne>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Knut Markhus |first= |last= |editor-first=Ottar |editor-last=Grepstad |editor-link=Ottar Grepstad |encyclopedia=Allkunne |publisher=Nynorsk kultursentrum |location= |url= https://www.allkunne.no/framside/biografiar/m/knut-markhus//96/726/ |language=Norwegian|accessdate=21 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Knut Olson Markhus |first= |last= |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |editor-last=Bolstad | editor-first=Erik | editor-link= |publisher=Norsk nettleksikon |location=Oslo |url=https://snl.no/Knut_Olson_Markhus |language=Norwegian |accessdate=21 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Knut Markhus |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Jarle |last=Bondevik |authorlink= |editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=https://nbl.snl.no/Knut_Markhus | language=Norwegian |accessdate=21 July 2018}}</ref>
