{{Infobox language |name = Nyali |nativename=''Linyali'' |states = [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]] |region = [[Ituri Province]] |speakers = 43,000 |date=1993 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo languages|Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Bantoid languages|Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] ([[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages#Zone D|Zone D.30]]) |fam6=[[Nyali languages|Nyali]] (Budu–Ndaka) |iso3=nlj |glotto=nyal1250 |glottorefname=Nyali |guthrie=D.33 }} '''Nyali''', or '''North Nyali''', is a minor [[Bantu language]] of the Democratic Republic of the Congo. It is lexically similar to [[Ndaka language|Ndaka]] and [[Budu language|Budu]], [[Mbo language (Congo)|Mbo]], and [[Vanuma language|Vanuma]] (South Nyali).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=zmw |work=Ethnologue |title=Mbo |accessdate=2011-10-13}}</ref>
